result.conclusion_template_zh: "Archetype" was synonymous with "Idea" in Platonic usage—pre-existent and supraordinate to phenomena.
There can be no empirical knowledge that is not already caught and limited by the a priori structure of cognition.
Preconscious psyche is NOT empty vessel—tremendously complicated individual entity.
Man's behaviour results from "images"—primordial patterns, the "human quality."
Archetypes can rearise spontaneously, at any time, without outside influence.
Present in every psyche: unconscious but active forms—living dispositions preforming thoughts.
Archetypes are not determined as regards their content, but only as regards their form—they correspond in every way to instincts.
Mother symbols include goddesses, Paradise, Church, earth, sea, moon, cave, well, vessels, mandala—and negative symbols like witch, dragon, grave, deep water.
All mother symbols can have positive or negative meaning—the goddesses of fate (Moira, Norns) embody ambivalence.

The mother archetype's qualities: maternal solicitude, magic authority, wisdom transcending reason, and all that cherishes and sustains—but also the abyss, the world of the dead, all that devours and poisons.
Personal mother has only limited significance—true influence is the archetype projected upon her.
Archetypes are inalienable assets; task is to dissolve projections, not deny archetypes.
Mother archetype is foundation of mother-complex—disturbed instincts constellate archetypes that come between child and mother.
In every masculine mother-complex, the anima plays a significant role alongside the mother archetype—the mother is the first feminine being for the man-to-be.
Positive effects: finely differentiated Eros, great friendship capacity, aesthetic sense, religious feelings, revolutionary spirit, heroism.
Type (a) Maternal hypertrophy: intensification of all female instincts, husband secondary, lives through children, unconscious will to power.
Type (b) Overdeveloped Eros: maternal instinct wiped out, unconscious incestuous relation with father, attracted to married men.
Type (c) Identity with mother: shadow-existence, sucked dry by mother, paralysis of feminine initiative, attractive as empty vessel.
Type (d) Resistance: "Anything so long as it is not like Mother!"—knows what she doesn't want but not her own fate.
Resistance to mother can result in spontaneous intellect development—to break mother's power by criticism.
Mother-love is the mysterious root of all growth and change—homecoming, shelter, the long silence from which everything begins and ends.
The archetype is less a scientific problem than an urgent question of psychic hygiene—without it, our highest values disappear into the unconscious.
Man must remain conscious of the world of archetypes because there he is part of Nature and connected with his own roots.
"The world was still in its primeval state; it did not know that it was. And then, in that one moment in which I came to know, the world sprang into being."
The Logos eternally struggles to extricate itself from the maternal womb—unconsciousness is the primal sin; its first act of liberation is matricide.
Emotion is the chief source of consciousness—there is no change from darkness to light without emotion.
Disturber is herself changed; what seemed senseless upheaval becomes purification.
Empty vessel filled by anima projection—Cherchez la femme, secret of his success.
Emptiness is great feminine secret—the yin. Such female is fate itself.
Negative type has best chance for marriage success in second half of life.
Mythology and mother-complex point to unconscious—man's cosmos division reflects conscious/unconscious polarity.
West split God: Yahweh
Nietzsche's Superman tried to imprison divine paradox in mortal man—burst asunder.
Man's mother-image is alien, symbolical; his idealization is hidden fear of unconscious.
Man = Urania type, identifies with puer aeternus; woman = chthonic, identifies with Earth Mother.
Syzygies lead to individuation—realm of immediate experience, terrifying paradox.
Psyche is empirical reality with powers of its own—not mere figure of speech.
Archetype = purely formal (facultas praeformandi); filled with experience becomes vivid image.
"精神"=多义词，约20种意义——物质对立面、生命原理、态度、时代精神、客观精神、鬼魂。
Spirit's wind-nature: active, winged, swift—dynamic principle vs matter's stasis.
Transcendent spirit became supranatural cosmic order, named "God."
Materialism: spirit = psychic functions dependent on brain/metabolism.
精神三标志：自发运动、自发产像、自主操控——动态原理vs物质的静止惰性。
精神具原型本质——智慧老人是最常见形式，在需要洞察理解但自己无法调动时出现。
老人在英雄绝望时出现——代表知识、智慧、善意，是精神功能的人格化。
Old man as dwarf = connection to unconscious; little iron man appears at critical junctures.
Unconscious = world of infinitesimally small; archetypes share this with atomic world—smallest causes, greatest effects.
老人与太阳/火=启明性质——精神的火焰面向。
原型有光明面和阴暗面——老人可能是自己的对立面，既赐生也予死。
审慎审查"善良老人"语境——他可能事先设置困境。
老人=女性的阿尼姆斯——阿尼姆斯附身导致囚禁。
动物形式=精神原型的超人领域表现——无意识悖论统一对立。
动物助手=精神原型的动物表达——说人语、超人智慧。
马=知识和直觉功能——精神既是功能也是自主主体。
三vs四=极性vs整体——每个三元组预设其对立。
四种心理功能——三可分化，一为劣势，阿喀琉斯之踵。
英雄=优势功能，猎人=劣势功能——最终合一。
Russian variant "Maria Morevna": three helpful animals = Ivan's three sisters married to bird-men (angelic helpers).
Three-legged horse = mare = unconscious masculinity in female = animus representing spirit.
Princess A (anima) possesses three-legged horse (shadow)—she has caught the hero on his weak side.
Four-legged horse = hunter's mount; quaternity = more conscious state; hero's claim is legitimate through witch's permission.
Two horses together = complete union of opposites: feminine triad (unconscious) + masculine quaternity (conscious).
Spirit archetype is ambivalent—can help or possess; the decisive factor is consciousness.
精神未脱魔性——科技发展增加被附身危险，善恶取决于有意识决定，无意识是人最大的罪。
Abandonment motif—archetypal theme of being left or forsaken.
The collective unconscious is a deeper layer that does not derive from personal experience but is inborn—universal in all humans.
For Freud, the unconscious is exclusively personal—nothing but the gathering place of forgotten and repressed contents.
The contents of the collective unconscious are known as archetypes—primordial types, universal images that have existed since the remotest times.
Personal unconscious contains feeling-toned complexes; collective unconscious contains archetypes.
"Archetype" occurs in Philo (Imago Dei), Irenaeus, Corpus Hermeticum—it is a paraphrase of the Platonic εἶδος.
Myth and fairytale express archetypes but are forms that have received a specific stamp—the archetype itself is prior to conscious elaboration.
Myths are first and foremost psychic phenomena that reveal the nature of the soul—not solar, lunar, or meteorological allegories.
The two magicians (white and black) are two aspects of the wise old man—spirit has light and dark sides.
"The stars of thine own fate lie in thy breast"—a dictum that should satisfy all astrologers if we knew the heart's secrets.
Tribal lore is always sacred and dangerous. All esoteric teachings seek to apprehend unseen happenings in the psyche.
We had a religious formula for everything psychic—more beautiful and comprehensive than immediate experience—so psychology is the youngest science.
Brother Klaus saw a sight so terrible that his countenance was permanently changed—people were terrified of him.
The mandala is the traditional antidote for chaotic states of mind—that is why Brother Klaus was fascinated by the symbol of the wheel.
Dogma proved its power of assimilation by turning something horribly alive into the beautiful abstraction of the Trinity idea.
Dogma takes the place of the collective unconscious by formulating its contents on a grand scale.
The Reformation's iconoclasm quite literally made a breach in the protective wall of sacred images—one image after another has crumbled away.
The history of Protestantism has been one of chronic iconoclasm—the alarming poverty of symbols is now the condition of our life.
Can we put on like new clothes ready-made symbols grown on foreign soil—resembling a beggar who wraps himself in kingly raiment?
It would be far better to avow our spiritual poverty, our symbol-lessness, instead of feigning a legacy to which we are not legitimate heirs.
When spirit becomes heavy it turns to water, and with Luciferian presumption the intellect usurps the seat where once the spirit was enthroned.
The way of the soul seeking its lost father—like Sophia seeking Bythos—leads to the water, to the dark mirror that reposes at its bottom.
A Protestant theologian often dreamed of a dark lake in a deep valley—something always prevented him from approaching until he resolved to go.
In the dream the wind, the pneuma, rushes over the water's face—hinting at an unseen presence, a numen that lives of itself.
We must go the way of waters, which always tend downward, if we would raise up the treasure, the precious heritage of the father.
Water is the commonest symbol for the unconscious—psychologically, water means spirit that has become unconscious.
The shadow is a tight passage, a narrow door, whose painful constriction no one is spared who goes down to the deep well.
The collective unconscious is sheer objectivity, as wide as the world—there I am the object of every subject.
The unconscious no sooner touches us than we are it—we become unconscious of ourselves. That is the age-old danger.
When symbols become weak with age, these barriers collapse—then the waters rise and boundless catastrophes break over mankind.
Today we call the gods "factors"—the makers stand behind the wings of the world-theatre.
Every man carries with him the eternal image of woman—a definite feminine image that is fundamentally unconscious, inherited, primordial.
Since this image is unconscious, it is always projected upon the beloved—one of the chief reasons for passionate attraction or aversion.
After the shadow comes the anima—she is the other, the complementary side.
The anima can be a siren, melusina, succubus, who infatuates young men and sucks the life out of them—or a witch mixing vile potions.
Soul is the living thing in man, that which lives of itself and causes life—Greek psyche means butterfly, quick-moving, twinkling.
The anima is a natural archetype, a "factor" that man cannot make—it is the a priori element in moods, reactions, and spontaneous psychic life.
Shadow encounter is the "apprentice-piece"; anima encounter is the "master-piece"—an ordeal by fire for spiritual and moral forces.
Archetypes are complexes of experience that come upon us like fate—it is no use at all to learn a list of archetypes by heart.
The wise old man is the superior master and teacher, the archetype of the spirit, symbolizing the pre-existent meaning hidden in the chaos of life.
All important ideas are founded on primordial archetypal forms—thought was revelation, forced upon us, not invented.
The white magician said: "For this we need the help of the black magician"—dressed in opposite colors, they are two aspects of the same archetype.
The old king is the ruling symbol that wants eternal rest—when he dies, the anima awakens as a black horse.
The black magician found the lost keys of paradise—the mandala is a symbol of individuation.
The old man is showing how good and evil function together—approaching the nirdvandva, freedom from opposites.
The standpoint of the unconscious is relative to the conscious attitude—the tendency to relativize opposites is a notable peculiarity.
If "Lucifer" (light-bringer) were not prejudicial, it would be a suitable name for this archetype of meaning.
Archetypes of transformation are not personalities but typical situations that symbolize transformation.
Symbolic process shows enantiodromian structure like I Ching—rhythm of opposites.
In all dissociation: integrate unconscious into consciousness—the "individuation process."
Archetypes require dialectical procedure—the alchemical meditatio: "inner colloquy with one's good angel."
Patient: "Surely you see the sun's penis—that is where the wind comes from."
Mithraic liturgy: "the tube, origin of ministering wind, hanging from the sun."
X小姐与阿尼姆斯生活，访问母亲国家激发绘画——第一幅画显示被困岩石，期望魔法解放。
石头转变为蛋——生命胚芽，哲学象征——无意识暗示个体化是解决方案。
闪电从黑暗混沌中炸出圆球——突然的心理状态改变——圆球=自性。
Eggs transformed into abstract spheres; magician's touch became lightning—rediscovering the rotundum, original form of Anthropos.
Böhme: "In this Spirit of the Fire-flash consists the Great Almighty Life." Flash = Birth of Light with transformative power.
Lightning caught in the four Qualities makes a Cross—pertaining to the Kingdom of Glory while Nature remains in darkness.
银带 = 水银 = 墨丘利翅膀 = 阿尼姆斯——在外面而不是里面，尚未整合。
The unconscious goes straight for its goal: allowing an individual to become whole—not a personal imbroglio.
Inferior function = deus ex machina, depends on self not ego; thrusts ego aside for totality. Self was always present but sleeping.
Gold = sunlight, value, divinity—the aurum philosophicum. Pyramids = unconscious contents pushing up into consciousness.
Number 12 = culminating point of life; this is the birth of the self, not of the dreamer.
"True personality" = Chinese chen-yen = alchemical homo quadratus; the "total" man is as big as the world like an Anthropos.
Primordial image: the world egg encoiled by a snake—the self entwined by the mercurial serpent.
Black serpent with golden Mercury wings = pneumatic nature; alchemists' Mercurius duplex.
Miss X's realization: "Ego was not the centre—following universal law, I circled round a sun."
Letting go is sine qua non of higher spiritual development; but holding fast requires conscious ego.
Swastika wheeling to the right = ascent into light of consciousness; philosophical tree = individuation process.
Mandala is a God-image: "God is an infinite circle whose centre is everywhere and circumference nowhere."
Cortices (layers of skin) = cabalistic klippoth; golden cross binds the four together as inner consolidation.
Four eddies coalesced into wavy squares; golden points emit rainbow colours = cauda pavonis.
Eye = prototype of mandala; Böhme calls it "Eye of the Wonders of Eternity"—animus had "seen things too blackly."
Accepting darkness = kindling a light that illuminates the darkness within.
Mandala divided: above, three white birds (Trinity); below, goat with ravens (Wotan's birds)—Western Christian background.
Böhme failed to unite opposites in mandala; Miss X succeeded aided by Chinese Yin-Yang doctrine.
Cancer sign appeared; 16 years later Miss X died of breast cancer—a synchronistic phenomenon at the climax of opposites.
Eye motif = polyophthalmia = "multiple consciousness" of the unconscious.
Nobody can tell the whole story of individuation—death speaks the final "consummatum est."
Masses are not changed unless the individual changes; bettering begins with individual responsibility.
How can consciousness be linked up again with the unconscious? Anyone who overlooks instincts will be ambuscaded by them.
Pathological reaction = identification with archetype
Mandala paintings are ideograms of unconscious contents—they develop out of themselves, often opposing conscious intentions.
Individuation subordinates the many to the One; the One is God; the God-image expresses itself in the mandala.
曼陀罗东西方普遍存在——自发出现于现代人梦境，表达对完整性和中心化的渴望。
East: meditation tool; West: rose windows; spontaneous in modern dreams/fantasies.
Particularly during psychological crisis or individuation process; relates to order/balance/wholeness.
曼陀罗代表自性——人格整体；制作或冥想带来平衡和安宁，是心灵自我调节机制。
Center = most sacred part; may be empty (formless divinity) or contain deity/symbol/geometry.
Creating/meditating on mandala
Child motif's universality was obscured by disciplinary fragmentation—psychology overlooked the nonconscious psyche until Carus.
原始心智不发明神话，而是经历神话——神话是前意识心灵的原初启示。
原型内容产生于意识强度降低的状态——梦、谵妄、幻想、幻觉——此时意识抑制停止，无意识如打开的侧闸涌入。
雅内的"心理水平下降"对应原始意识状态——神话最初就在此状态中形成，与今天个体中原型显现相似。
每种原型解释必然是"似乎"——意义核心可界定但不可描述。
现代文学中永恒少年仍以新形式出现——证明童子原型的持久生命力。
原型没有理性替代物——如小脑或肾脏不能被替代，必须问目的论问题：原型的生物学目的是什么？
童子母题代表集体心灵的前意识、童年方面——不是个人童年记忆，而是人类共同的心理遗产。
宗教仪式将童年意象一次又一次呈现在意识眼前——以使与原初状态的联系不被打断。
童子母题是当下运作的系统——目的是补偿或修正意识心智不可避免的片面性和极端性。
保守理想更原始、自然、道德；进步理想更抽象、不自然——意志强制的进步总是痉挛性的。
童子的本质特征是未来性——童子是潜在的未来，预期未来发展，为人格变化铺路。
复数童子无个体特征=解离可能，见于精神分裂症——众多童子代表人格瓦解产物。
单一童子=无意识且暂时完成的人格综合——如一切无意识，仅意味着可能性。
童神完全超自然，人格化未整合的集体无意识；童英雄是半神，代表意识与无意识的综合。
奇迹诞生描绘自性起源的体验方式——心理起源必须非经验地发生。
"比小更小，比大更大"悖论是英雄本质——能应对最大危险，却被微不足道之物毁灭。
从对立碰撞中，无意识创造第三种非理性东西——既非"是"也非"否"，被双方拒绝。
童子=向独立进化；遗弃是必要条件，非仅症状——必须与起源分离才能独立。
童子神话悖论：无助+危险 vs 超凡力量——微不足道却神圣，将意外渡过难关。
象征越古老/深/生理学
雌雄同体=最强对立面的统一——从原初非分化转化为"统一象征"，指向未来目标。
原型因统一对立的力量在无意识与意识之间调解——在当今意识与原始整体性之间架起桥梁。
双性原初存在转化为自性象征——对立面战争找到和平，成为自我发展的遥远目标。
Coniunctio in Gnosticism as mysterium iniquitatis; Gospel of Egyptians: "When two shall be one, male with female neither male nor female."
Hermaphrodite in modern psychology = male-female antithesis; woman has animus (masculine unconscious), man has anima.
Archetype evolved from fertility magic
童子=开端+终结，初始+终端生物——象征前意识本质和后意识本质。
整体性=全包，超越意识范围——比意识更老更年轻，在时空上包裹意识。
永恒童子=不可描述经验+不协调+障碍+神圣特权——决定人格终极价值的不可衡量者。
没有原型可简化为公式——是永远倒不空填不满的容器，只有潜在存在，需不断重新诠释。
心理学使用源自原型结构的观念——产生一种更抽象的神话，是科学神话的元素。
童子原型在个体化中三阶段：童稚认同
绕过英雄认同后意识与无意识分离和解综合——人格中心从自我转移到自性。
四个童子母题——遗弃、不可战胜、雌雄同体、开端与终结——作为不同经验和理解类别各就其位。
Psychosis differs from neurosis: unconscious contents utterly strange, ego swamped by them.
Autonomy of unconscious begins with emotions—instinctive, involuntary, upsetting rational order.
Unconscious = reality in potentia; conscious thinks in years, unconscious in millennia.
Unconscious is the mother of consciousness—ego was born out of it.
Unconscious often truer and wiser than conscious; fate depends on it.
Unconscious collaboration is intelligent, purposive, compensatory.
If fragments have personality, the whole must have it to higher degree.
Anima (in man) and animus (in woman) = contrasexual unconscious personality.
Shadow = personal unconscious, personifies refused inferior traits.
Individuation = fair fight between conscious and unconscious; hammer and anvil forging "individual."
Union of opposites = "transcendent function"—goal of psychotherapy beyond symptom cure.
骗术师特征：恶作剧、变形、双重性、受折磨、近救世主——墨丘利是典型组合。
骚灵=超心理学中的骗术师平行物——围绕青春期前儿童的恶作剧和低智力通信。
骗术师与圣人=补偿关系——无意义转化为有意义揭示这一关系。
中世纪愚人节=古代农神节的教会版——等级颠倒、下流行为、化装舞蹈。
Trickster is a psychologem—archetypal structure of extreme antiquity, reflecting undifferentiated consciousness barely above animal level.
Trickster motif appears in modern man's "accidents"—I call this component the shadow.
Trickster is forerunner of saviour; his sufferings are real and therapeutic—through laughter man rises above his predicament.
文明化过程在骗术师循环内开始——原始状态被克服，行为变有用明智。
文明人遗忘骗术师——不知阴影危险，群众聚集时阴影被动员并可肉身化。
骗术师神话有治疗效果——使人不忘早期状态，两种矛盾倾向并存。
骗术师=集体阴影=所有低劣特征总和——个体阴影从不缺席，集体形象不断构建。
救世主暗示=灾难被意识理解——阴影整合创造痛苦处境，只有救世主能解开。
个体阴影含向对立面转化种子——意识发展带来从无意识囚禁的解放。
Kore的心理学对应：自性/超位人格+阿尼玛——三相女神是无意识心理学的实际问题。
原型只在习惯性语境中清晰——抽象本质会使之模糊，需让其保持有机整体。
现象学方法是研究心理现象的唯一可行途径——描述和分类优于过早解释。
Kore在男性中=阿尼玛，在女性中=超位人格——心理形象本质双重双极。
超位人格=完整的人=真正的人——包括无意识心灵及其要求和需要。
自性象征：人类形象、兽形、植物、几何形象——从动物到神圣补充人格描述。
母女原型向上向下延伸女性意识——每个母亲包含女儿，每个女儿包含母亲，超越时间达永恒。
得墨忒耳崇拜=净化+再生——现代文化缺乏厄琉息斯式心理卫生。
积极想象=观察内在图像流的内省方法——集中注意、观察变化、悬置批评、客观记录。
案例X白鸟幻象——麦子、蓝衣女神、母亲原型。
公牛与孩童——欧罗巴形式、球游戏与儿童献祭母题。
青年与少女=配对/合一——阿尼姆斯整合象征整体性。
海底蛇穴神圣女性=地母原型——皮肤黝黑、红唇、巨大力量。
光明与麦田=启示——白火在头上舞动，母亲篇章结束。
天空女人与熊=超位人格双重性——正面保护，负面本能，需整合。
Ursanna神殿=熊女神+圣母合一——四位一体结构象征自性。
月亮女士vs大地母亲——上方推动冒险，下方保护接住，做梦者扮演科瑞角色。
男性中科瑞=阿尼玛——双极性，与神秘/黑暗有隐秘联系，在时间之外。
案例Z阿尼玛变形——鸟、蛇、女神、老妇，展示无意识的流动性和矛盾性。
得墨忒耳-科瑞=母权社会秩序——男性不可或缺但令人不安。
曼陀罗是圆形图像，代表自性——人格整体，自发出现于心理转折点，提供整合与保护。
Kundalini: Shakti as snake wound round lingam (Shiva); creation begins with division of opposites united in deity.
Basic motif: premonition of personality centre—the self (not ego), source of energy to which everything is related.
Perfect union of all energies = Diamond Body (Chinese), corpus incorruptibile (medieval), corpus glorificationis (Christian).
Mandala formal elements: circle/sphere/egg, flower/wheel, centre with rays, rotation, snake, squaring of circle, temenos, eye.
The inner spiral = Kundalini snake winding three and a half times round the centre stone.
蛇人格化无意识本身，鱼代表其内容——鱼更分化，历史上有更高权威（Ichthys）。
鱼在无意识海洋制造漩涡，在中心形成珍贵珍珠——难以获得的宝藏。
Penelope-like weaving of magic circle as counterbalance to life's difficulties—protective against tension of opposites.
Snake = unconscious itself (primitive); fish = its contents (differentiated). Two different stages of development.
Three phases of individuation: chthonic roots below, cultivating mind in middle, reborn receiving illumination at top.
Liverpool dream: red-flowering magnolia in everlasting sunshine amidst dark city—became ruby rose, "window opening on to eternity."
Four animals at cardinal points = instinctive forces brought into unity; integration of instincts is prerequisite for individuation.
孔雀=凤凰，从火中重生——cauda pavonis是所有颜色，整体性的展开和实现。
Five = natural man; four = spiritual man. The dilemma of four and five corresponds to the conflict between culture and nature.
Children's circle drawings function as protective magic circles—self-protection against outer difficulties.
Behind the mandala lurks the devil—the shadow aspect represents the chaos that hides behind the self.
Divine Child = child enclosed in revolving sphere = Hiranyagarbha = homunculus.
Breaking lines in schizoid mandala = evil/destructive impulses; regular structure restrains dissociation.
Birth of new insight (eye) from depths of unconscious (sea); eye = the self.
曼陀罗为心理混乱提供秩序，为分裂人格提供整合——制作过程本身就是治疗。
Sanskrit mandala means 'circle'—best and most significant mandalas are found in Tibetan Buddhism.
Mandala as yantra (instrument of contemplation)—aids concentration by narrowing psychic field to the centre.
A drastic revolution by Fechner and Wundt was needed to show that psychology was a field of experience, not philosophical theory.
Freud cleared ground only so far as physiological concepts permitted—psychology looked like an offshoot of physiology.
The psyche does not end where physiological assumption stops—we must consider manifestations in their totality.
The concept of the anima is a purely empirical concept, whose sole purpose is to give a name to a group of related psychic phenomena—not theoretical invention.
The psychic factor must be regarded as an autonomous reality of enigmatic character—psychic processes cannot be fabricated in a retort.
In classical Chinese philosophy, the anima (p'o or kuei) is regarded as the feminine and chthonic part of the soul.
We encounter the anima in the divine syzygies, male-female pairs of deities—yang and yin—as universal as the existence of man and woman.
It is more embarrassing to talk about God at table than to tell a risqué story—admitting analyst is saviour seems pathological.
Materialism, atheism, communism, socialism, existentialism—all are dominating représentations collectives, proving no one escapes religious ideas.
The archetype behind religious ideas has its specific energy, which it does not lose even if the conscious mind ignores it.
Projection is an unconscious, automatic process whereby a content transfers itself to an object, so that it seems to belong to that object—it ceases when made conscious.
Projection is never conscious: projections are always there first and are recognized afterwards.
Brother Klaus saw God in dual form—majestic father AND jung_majestic mother—could not be more unorthodox, proving spontaneous archetypal vision.
The syzygy motif expresses that masculine is always paired with feminine—its wide distribution and emotionality prove it is a fundamental psychic factor.
It is a great mistake to suppose the newborn psyche is a tabula rasa—the child meets stimuli with specific inherited aptitudes, the archetypes.
Archetypes are strongest where consciousness is weakest—they anthropomorphize reality most where fantasy can overrun facts.
The mother was first a divine hermaphrodite, then through reality's disappointment, changed into an ordinary old woman—this was the patient's "castration."
"Fear of castration" was fear of real life, which refused to come up to childish expectations and lacked mythological meaning—life became "godless."
Godparents represent the pair of gods who appear at birth—the "dual birth" motif preserving connection to archetypal stage.
Nobody can stand total loss of the archetype—when that happens, it gives rise to frightful "discontent in culture" where nobody feels at home.
Archetype in quiescent state has no determinable form—assumes definite form only in projection.
Empirically = types; but basic psychic elements infinitely varied—empiricist uses theoretical "as if."
The anima intensifies, exaggerates, falsifies, and mythologizes all emotional relations—when constellated, she makes a man touchy, moody, jealous, maladjusted.
Before midlife, a man can bear total anima loss—the important thing is for a man to be a man, freeing from mother's fascination.
After midlife, permanent anima loss means diminution of vitality, flexibility, human kindness—premature rigidity or resignation.
Beyond personal consciousness exists a second psychic system of collective, universal, impersonal nature—identical in all individuals.
This collective unconscious does not develop individually but is inherited; it consists of pre-existent forms, the archetypes.
The collective unconscious is deeper than personal unconscious—a universal inherited stratum present at birth.
Explains why humans across all cultures produce similar myths, symbols, dreams despite no contact.
Unlike Freud's purely personal unconscious, Jung adds a transpersonal layer—species-wide, not individual.
Beneath cultural differences lies a shared symbolic substrate—the psychic unity of humankind.
Archetypes are not determined as regards their content, but only as regards their form—a possibility of representation given a priori.
Form compared to axial system of crystal, preforming structure in mother liquid though having no material existence.
The archetype in itself is empty and purely formal—nothing but a facultas praeformandi.
Archetype is pre-existent formal pattern—not fixed image but potential for certain types of images.
When archetype constellates powerfully, produces numinous experience—overwhelming, fascinating, beyond personal control.
Individuation means becoming an 'in-dividual'—becoming one's own self, self-realization.
The aim is to divest the self of false wrappings of persona and the suggestive power of primordial images.
Mid-life crisis triggers inward turn when persona no longer satisfies and unconscious demands attention.
Goal is ego-Self axis—conscious ego relating appropriately to larger Self, maintaining distinction while in dialogue.
Process makes you MORE individual (unique) yet MORE connected (to collective unconscious, humanity).
The shadow is a moral problem that challenges the whole ego-personality, for no one can become conscious of the shadow without considerable moral effort.
To become conscious of it involves recognizing the dark aspects of the personality as present and real.
This act is the essential condition for any kind of self-knowledge, and it therefore meets with considerable resistance.
Shadow is "dark brother"—rejected sibling seeking recognition and integration, not annihilation.
Men carry within them an inner feminine (anima), women carry an inner masculine (animus)—contrasexual archetypes inherited through collective unconscious.
We fall in love with someone who carries our anima/animus projection—passionate attraction = encountering own unconscious contrasexual side externalized.
Integration goal is psychological androgyny—healthy human is both masculine and feminine, not one-sided.
When projection withdraws (infatuation fades), real relationship begins—or relationship ends.
The self is not only the centre but also the whole circumference which embraces both conscious and unconscious.
The ego is, by definition, subordinate to the self and is related to it like a part to the whole.
The Self appears in dreams as mandalas (circles, squares, quaternity), God-images, trees, mountains, wise old man, divine child.
Individuation aims at ego-Self axis—conscious ego relating appropriately to larger Self, servant not master.
Two fundamental attitudes: extraversion (energy flows outward toward objects) and introversion (energy flows inward toward subject).
Everyone possesses both attitudes but one dominates as superior; the inferior attitude operates unconsciously.
Psychic energy orientation determines personality's basic stance—outward engagement or inward reflection.
Four functions of consciousness: Thinking and Feeling are rational/judging; Sensation and Intuition are irrational/perceiving.
These form two pairs of opposites: Thinking↔Feeling (rational axis), Sensation↔Intuition (irrational axis).
Function hierarchy: Superior (most developed)
Coniunctio is the alchemical symbol for union of opposites—King and Queen, Sol and Luna, conscious and unconscious.
Psychologically, it represents integration of ego with Self, union of masculine and feminine within individual.
Union of Sol (consciousness) and Luna (unconscious) produces the Divine Child—the individuated Self.
Synchronicity is the occurrence of two or more causally unrelated events experienced as occurring together in a meaningful manner.
It points to a deeper order connecting psyche and matter—the Unus Mundus (one world) underlying both domains.
Inner psychic event coincides with outer physical event, connected by meaning not mechanism—foundation for divination theory.
The alchemical opus proceeds through distinct stages: nigredo (blackening), albedo (whitening), and rubedo (reddening).
Transformation requires nigredo—no rebirth without death of old form; dissolution of old self precedes integration.
These stages correspond psychologically to individuation—nigredo (shadow work), albedo (purification), rubedo (final integration).
The transcendent function arises from union of conscious and unconscious contents—a psychic process that creates a third thing, a symbol.
It emerges when ego holds tension between opposites without choosing either pole—allowing unconscious to contribute.
The symbol transcends both poles, creating new conscious position integrating what seemed irreconcilable.
